items.title: How To Earn $500 A Month From Procter & Gamble Stock Ahead Of Q3 Earnings
items.description: Procter & Gamble Company (NYSE:PG) will release third-quarter earnings results before the opening bell on Thursday, April 24. Analysts expect the Cincinnati, Ohio-based company to report quarterly earnings at $1.53 per share, up from $1.52 per share in the year-ago period. Procter & Gamble projects to report quarterly revenue at $20.15 billion, compared to $20.2 billion a year earlier, according to data from Benzinga Pro.
